WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.640 --> 00:00:04.200
Barclays Online Banking

2
00:00:04.800 --> 00:00:07.520
How to reset your passcode and memorable word

3
00:00:09.200 --> 00:00:12.040
It's easy to reset your
Online Banking passcode.

4
00:00:12.960 --> 00:00:15.200
To start click ‘Log In’.

5
00:00:16.360 --> 00:00:19.680
Next, type in your surname as
it appears on your account.

6
00:00:20.760 --> 00:00:24.200
Then select one of the options
and type in your details.

7
00:00:24.800 --> 00:00:26.200
Click ‘Continue’.

8
00:00:27.120 --> 00:00:29.800
Then click ‘Don't know your passcode?’

9
00:00:30.520 --> 00:00:32.280
Enter your date of birth.

10
00:00:32.800 --> 00:00:35.040
Now select the type of
account you have

11
00:00:35.480 --> 00:00:37.600
and enter your account details,

12
00:00:38.920 --> 00:00:41.520
followed by your 3-digit security code.

13
00:00:42.240 --> 00:00:43.960
Next, click ‘Continue’.

14
00:00:45.960 --> 00:00:49.520
This screen provides you with two
options to reset your passcode.

15
00:00:51.120 --> 00:00:54.560
For this example, we'll choose
‘Send me a text message’.

16
00:00:55.120 --> 00:00:56.960
If you have more than one mobile number,

17
00:00:57.360 --> 00:00:59.920
select the one you'd like us to
send the text message to

18
00:01:00.040 --> 00:01:01.480
and click ‘Continue’.

19
00:01:03.160 --> 00:01:06.160
You should then receive a code by
text to your mobile phone

20
00:01:07.040 --> 00:01:10.360
but if there are any issues,
select ‘Request another code’.

21
00:01:11.640 --> 00:01:13.320
Next, click ‘Continue’

22
00:01:13.640 --> 00:01:15.920
and enter your new passcode twice.

23
00:01:17.880 --> 00:01:21.520
You'll now need a new memorable word
that you'll need to enter twice.

24
00:01:23.680 --> 00:01:26.240
Finally, click on ‘Confirm Passcode’

25
00:01:27.840 --> 00:01:31.000
and you can now use these
new details to login.

